  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is Code Splitting?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Code splitting is a technique that breaks large JavaScript bundles into smaller chunks. These chunks are loaded only when needed, reducing initial load time."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Use Code Splitting?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Loading a large bundle at once can slow down your website. Code splitting improves performance by loading only the required code for each page or feature."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Example (Dynamic Import)"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "import('./module.js').then(module => {\n  module.loadFeature();\n});"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Route-Based Code Splitting"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Load different JavaScript files for different routes instead of loading everything at once."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "const Home = () => import('./Home.js');\nconst About = () => import('./About.js');"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Component-Based Splitting"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Load components only when they are needed instead of bundling them all together."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "const LazyComponent = React.lazy(() => import('./MyComponent'));"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Benefits of Code Splitting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Faster initial page load**",
        "**Reduced bundle size**",
        "**Better caching efficiency**",
        "**Improved user experience**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "When to Use Code Splitting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Large applications with many features**",
        "**Multiple routes/pages**",
        "**Heavy third-party libraries**",
        "**Dynamic content loading**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Split code at route level**",
        "**Avoid too many small chunks**",
        "**Use caching effectively**",
        "**Combine with lazy loading**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Over-splitting code into too many chunks**",
        "**Not handling loading states**",
